</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> Replace printheadEvaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">When a printhead is installed visually check the matrix plate if all printheads are aligned.
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">The uniformity of a print is determined by the position of the ink droplets on the media. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The position of the droplets is controlled by the moment the droplet is jetted from the printhead. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">As the surface of the printhead is parallel to the surface of the media the time a droplet will take to reach the media is equal over the printhead. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">However if a printhead is not positioned well the time on the left side might be different than on the right side. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This will lead to mispositioning of the droplets on the media and results in a gloss gradient. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Under normal circumstances a small deviation in positioning error can be removed by printhead calibration. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-BDE42A10-0DAA-46D3-99F7-D18695E3843E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
